You are here:

Encrypt Application Form Seller Item Fields

Client application form and a seller product sometimes contain sensitive or personally identifiable information (PII). On the Application Form Seller Item object, you can now encrypt the Vehicle Identification Number, Engine Number, Vehicle Registration Number, Property Address, Scheduled Delivery Date, Property Unit Identifier, Make, Model, and Trim fields.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions where Financial Services Cloud is enabled.

Who: This change is available to customers with the Salesforce Shield or Shield Platform Encryption add-on subscriptions.

How: On the Encryption Settings page, click Select Fields. Click Edit, and then select the fields of the Application Form Seller Item object that you want to encrypt.
title: Encrypting Sensitive Data on Salesforce Application Forms
